{"article_id":"L4Ytw4BxD1GzHUaa","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Senate Democrats triggered the \" nuclear option \" Thursday ,","depth":5},{"id":1,"text":"using a shortcut","depth":7},{"id":2,"text":"to undercut the chamber ' s filibuster rules","depth":7},{"id":3,"text":"and giving President Obama a clear path","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"to stack the federal judiciary with ideological allies .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"In a tense 52-48 vote , Democrats overturned decades of precedent","depth":7},{"id":6,"text":"and reduced the number of votes","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"needed","depth":11},{"id":8,"text":"to cut off the filibuster of a nominee","depth":11},{"id":9,"text":"from 60 to a simple majority","depth":9},{"id":10,"text":"- and in the process tinkering with a tool","depth":9},{"id":11,"text":"that has made the Senate unique .","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"Republicans were hinting at retaliation","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"and said","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"the move further poisoned the atmosphere on Capitol Hill .","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid , Nevada Democrat , said","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"he didn ' t fear retaliation .","depth":8},{"id":17,"text":"He said","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"he reached a tipping point","depth":9},{"id":19,"text":"after Republicans filibustered three of Mr. Obama ' s nominees","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"to serve on the federal appeals court in Washington ,","depth":11},{"id":21,"text":"which is considered the second most important court in the country","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"because it hears cases","depth":13},{"id":23,"text":"involving key federal agencies .","depth":13},{"id":24,"text":"\" It ' s time to change .","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"It ' s time to change the Senate","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"before this institution becomes obsolete , \"","depth":11},{"id":27,"text":"Mr. Reid said","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"as he pushed his colleagues to coalesce on the critical vote .","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"Indeed , it was a vote","depth":10},{"id":30,"text":"many of them","depth":12},{"id":31,"text":"- particularly the newer Democratic members -","depth":12},{"id":32,"text":"have been anticipating .","depth":11},{"id":33,"text":"Frustrated by Republicans ' repeated ability","depth":11},{"id":34,"text":"to thwart Mr. Obama through the filibuster ,","depth":11},{"id":35,"text":"they have been pushing Mr. Reid to limit filibusters of nominees and legislation .","depth":10},{"id":36,"text":"The action , however , limits filibusters to nominees","depth":10},{"id":37,"text":"and doesn ' t apply to Supreme Court picks ,","depth":11},{"id":38,"text":"which Democrats deemed important enough","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"to be subject to a 60-vote threshold .","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"Indeed , hours after the rules change ,","depth":8},{"id":41,"text":"Republicans and Democrats filibustered the annual defense policy bill ,","depth":8},{"id":42,"text":"saying","depth":8},{"id":43,"text":"they wanted to extend the debate","depth":9},{"id":44,"text":"to make sure","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"their amendments get fair consideration .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"Thirty-two senators , more than half of the 52","depth":8},{"id":47,"text":"who voted for the rule change ,","depth":8},{"id":48,"text":"have never served in a Republican-majority Senate .","depth":7},{"id":49,"text":"Of those , 11 took office in January","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"and have not served for even a year in the chamber .","depth":7},{"id":51,"text":"\" They don ' t know","depth":8},{"id":52,"text":"what it ' s like to be in the minority ,","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"so they want to have a majority","depth":8},{"id":54,"text":"that will ride roughshod over the wishes and views and input of the minority , \"","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"Sen. John McCain , Arizona Republican , told reporters .","depth":6},{"id":56,"text":"\" Now","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"because of the partisanship and the new people","depth":10},{"id":58,"text":"who have never been in the minority ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"we are proving one thing ,","depth":9},{"id":60,"text":"and that is ,","depth":8},{"id":61,"text":"if the majority only can change the rules ,","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"then there are no rules , \"","depth":9},{"id":63,"text":"Mr. McCain said .","depth":6},{"id":64,"text":"\" That ' s the lesson here . \"","depth":5},{"id":65,"text":"Exactly how far Mr. Reid ' s move reverberates will depend on Republicans .","depth":4},{"id":66,"text":"Even without a full filibuster ,","depth":6},{"id":67,"text":"the minority has plenty of other tools","depth":7},{"id":68,"text":"to slow operations in the Senate .","depth":7},{"id":69,"text":"The level of partisanship Thursday seemed to remain .","depth":6},{"id":70,"text":"Despite the heated floor speeches ,","depth":7},{"id":71,"text":"Republicans and Democrats chatted amicably with one another on the floor ,","depth":8},{"id":72,"text":"and the top lawmakers on various committees were talking through details .","depth":8},{"id":73,"text":"At the White House , President Obama welcomed the change .","depth":5},{"id":74,"text":"As a senator , he regularly participated in filibusters ,","depth":7},{"id":75,"text":"including when Democrats pioneered the blockade of judicial nominees under President George W. Bush .","depth":7},{"id":76,"text":"But Mr. Obama said","depth":8},{"id":77,"text":"Republicans ' use of the filibuster is worse .","depth":8},{"id":78,"text":"\" It ' s no longer used in a responsible way","depth":10},{"id":79,"text":"to govern .","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"It ' s rather used as a reckless and relentless tool","depth":11},{"id":81,"text":"to grind all business to a halt .","depth":11},{"id":82,"text":"And that ' s not what our founders intended ,","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"and it ' s certainly not what our country needs right now , \"","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"he said .","depth":8},{"id":85,"text":"In the near term , the move will help speed through Mr. Obama ' s nominees for chairman of the Federal Reserve and secretary of the Homeland Security Department .","depth":5},{"id":86,"text":"Down the road , the changes could help Mr. Obama win confirmation on some of the more obscure but powerful federal boards","depth":6},{"id":87,"text":"that issue rules and decisions","depth":7},{"id":88,"text":"that make up much of the work of the federal government .","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"The timing of the vote struck Republicans as suspicious ,","depth":3},{"id":90,"text":"particularly because the numbers show","depth":5},{"id":91,"text":"that Republicans have not filibustered many of Mr. Obama ' s judicial picks .","depth":5},{"id":92,"text":"Indeed , until the most recent push","depth":6},{"id":93,"text":"to put judges on the D.C. appeals court ,","depth":6},{"id":94,"text":"Republicans had helped confirm 215 judges","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"and filibustered just two .","depth":6},{"id":96,"text":"Senate Minority Leader Mitch McConnell , Kentucky Republican , said","depth":6},{"id":97,"text":"Democrats are reeling from a disastrous rollout of Obamacare","depth":7},{"id":98,"text":"and needed to try to change the headlines .","depth":7},{"id":99,"text":"\" There ' s a lot of nervousness on the Democrat side .","depth":8},{"id":100,"text":"They ' re in a panic about Obamacare .","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"The majority leader is desperately trying to change the subject .","depth":8},{"id":102,"text":"We want to get back on the subject , \"","depth":8},{"id":103,"text":"Mr. McConnell said .","depth":6},{"id":104,"text":"Three Democrats voted against the change :","depth":6},{"id":105,"text":"Michigan ' s Carl Levin , Arkansas ' Mark L. Pryor and West Virginia ' s Joe Manchin III .","depth":6},{"id":106,"text":"\" Today ' s use of the ' nuclear option ' could permanently damage the Senate","depth":8},{"id":107,"text":"and have negative ramifications for the American people , \"","depth":8},{"id":108,"text":"Mr. Pryor said .","depth":7},{"id":109,"text":"\" During my time in the Senate , I ' ve played key roles in the Gang of 14 and other bipartisan coalitions","depth":8},{"id":110,"text":"to help us reach common-sense solutions","depth":9},{"id":111,"text":"that both sides of the aisle can support .","depth":9},{"id":112,"text":"This institution was designed","depth":8},{"id":113,"text":"to protect","depth":10},{"id":114,"text":"- not stamp out -","depth":10},{"id":115,"text":"the voices of the minority . \"","depth":9},{"id":116,"text":"Mr. Reid ' s move is known as the nuclear option","depth":7},{"id":117,"text":"because it requires complex parliamentary procedures and changing the rules in the middle of the session through a simple majority vote .","depth":7},{"id":118,"text":"The Senate usually must change its rules through a two-thirds vote ,","depth":7},{"id":119,"text":"which is one way","depth":9},{"id":120,"text":"the chamber enforces comity","depth":9},{"id":121,"text":"- something","depth":9},{"id":122,"text":"that sets it apart from the partisan House of Representatives .","depth":9},{"id":123,"text":"The new rules don ' t technically end the filibuster ,","depth":7},{"id":124,"text":"but they reduce the vote total","depth":10},{"id":125,"text":"needed","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"to cut off a filibuster","depth":11},{"id":127,"text":"from 60 to a simple majority","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"- the same level","depth":9},{"id":129,"text":"needed for confirmation .","depth":9},{"id":130,"text":"The chamber still will have to abide by the time limits","depth":8},{"id":131,"text":"that accompany filibusters ,","depth":8},{"id":132,"text":"which allow for up to 30 hours of debate","depth":8},{"id":133,"text":"once a filibuster has been defeated .","depth":8},{"id":134,"text":"Senate Republicans came close to doing a similar sort of rules change in 2005 ,","depth":6},{"id":135,"text":"when Democrats pioneered the practice","depth":7},{"id":136,"text":"of filibustering Mr. Bush ' s appeals court nominees .","depth":7},{"id":137,"text":"Republicans backed down","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"when a bipartisan group emerged","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"and settled on a gentleman ' s agreement","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"that headed off the rules change","depth":9},{"id":141,"text":"but preserved the right","depth":10},{"id":142,"text":"to filibuster .","depth":10}],"relations":[{"parent":285,"left":231,"right":284,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":231,"left":207,"right":230,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":207,"left":188,"right":206,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":188,"left":147,"right":187,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":147,"left":0,"right":146,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":146,"left":144,"right":145,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":144,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":145,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":187,"left":158,"right":186,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":158,"left":153,"right":157,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":153,"left":5,"right":152,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":152,"left":150,"right":151,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":150,"left":149,"right":9,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":149,"left":6,"right":148,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":148,"left":7,"right":8,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":151,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":157,"left":155,"right":156,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":155,"left":12,"right":154,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":154,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":156,"left":15,